You may need to implement a specialize `ArrayList` that is `Parcelable` for this to work. https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16493092/how-to-implement-parcelable-for-a-class-containing-listliststring The accepted answer here is good but you may want to use generics so it can used for more than just `String` or in your instance `Double`


As a side note you may want to look into a single layer solution for you coordinates something like this.

    public class Coordinates implements Parcelable{
        public double x;
        public double y;
        public double z;
        // You get the gist
    }
    List&lt;Coordinates&gt; coordinates = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

If you can do this you could avoid the above problem altogether. Again I have no clue about your setup and I could be completely wrong BUT a nested nested `List` is not the prettiest thing in the world.

